ErrorIndex.title: Wrapper for index information inside an error.

ErrorResponse.description: Generic error response for REST APIs

code.description: the numeric HTTP error code for the response.

details.description: The optional details of the error response.

dictionary.description:
Dictionary/map of associated data/information relevant to the error.
The error "message" may contain {{name}} escapes that should be substituted
with information from this dictionary.

domain.description:
The "domain" for the error.  If empty, it is an EDA
core error.  Alternatively it can be an EDA application
"apiVersion" value (e.g. interfaces.eda.nokia.com/v1alpha1)
indicating that the error is specific to that application.
The domain gives the receiver information that they can use
to help them interpret the "internal" error code value, or
to find an internationalization translation for the message.

errors.description:
Collection of errors in cases where more than one exists. This needs to be
flexible so we can support multiple formats

internal.description: Internal error code in cases where we don't have an array of errors

message.description: The basic text error message for the error response.

ref.description: Reference to the error source. Should typically be the URI of the request

type.description:
URI pointing at a document that describes the error and mitigation steps
If there is no document, point to the RFC for the HTTP error code

Status.title: Status is a return value for calls that don't return other objects.

com.nokia.eda.snmp.v1alpha1.ClusterDesti.description: ClusterDestination is the Schema for the clusterdestinations API

x-eda-nokia-com.ui-pattern-error: The apiVersion must be set to snmp.eda.nokia.com/v1alpha1
The kind must be set to ClusterDestination

spec.description: ClusterDestinationSpec defines the desired state of ClusterDestination

address.description:
Address is the IP address and port of the SNMP trap receiver.
Format: "<host>:<port>" (e.g., "192.0.2.1:162").

authentication.description:
Authentication contains the protocol and password used to authenticate SNMPv3 messages.
Required if SecurityLevel is "auth-no-priv" or "auth-priv".

password.description: Password is the authentication password for SNMPv3.

community.description:
Community is the SNMP community string for SNMPv2c.
Ignored for SNMPv3. Acts as a simple shared password in SNMPv2c.

engineID.description:
EngineID is the unique identifier of the remote SNMP engine.
Used in SNMPv3 for secure communication and context identification.

privacy.description:
Privacy contains the encryption protocol and password for securing SNMPv3 messages.
Required if SecurityLevel is "auth-priv".

password.description: Password is the encryption password for SNMPv3.

securityLevel.description:
SecurityLevel defines the security level for SNMPv3 communication.
Required for SNMPv3 only.
Supported values:
- "no-auth-no-priv": no authentication, no privacy
- "auth-no-priv": authentication only
- "auth-priv": authentication and privacy (encryption)

supportInformPDU.description: If true the destination supports Inform PDUs.

user.description:
User is the SNMPv3 username used for authentication and privacy.
Required for SNMPv3 when using "auth-no-priv" or "auth-priv" levels.

version.description:
Version specifies the SNMP protocol version to use for trap messages.
Supported values: "v1", "v2c", "v3".
